Add a public function called DoWhileDemo to Effects.calr that demonstrates a do-while loop. The function takes no parameters and returns void. It should print at least once before checking the condition.

Use this exact Calor do-while syntax:
§F{f001:DoWhileDemo:pub}
  §O{void}
  §E{cw}
  §B{x} 0
  §DO{d001}
    §C{Console.WriteLine}
      §A x
    §/C
    §ASSIGN x (+ x 1)
  §/DO{d001} (< x 3)
§/F{f001}

The §DO{id}...§/DO{id} (condition) syntax creates a do-while loop where:
- id is a unique loop identifier (d001)
- The body executes at least once
- condition is checked at the end
